{"id":4183,"date":"2016-11-10T17:31:04","date_gmt":"2016-11-11T01:31:04","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/sfifoundation.com\/?p=4183"},"modified":"2016-11-10T17:31:04","modified_gmt":"2016-11-11T01:31:04","slug":"notice-of-counterfeit-drivers-gear","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/sfifoundation.com\/notice-of-counterfeit-drivers-gear\/","title":{"rendered":"NOTICE OF COUNTERFEIT DRIVER&#8217;S GEAR"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>The photos below are examples of recently discovered counterfeit SFI conformance labels attached to shoes and driver suits fraudulently represented as being certified to SFI specifications.<\/p>\n<p>These were found on non-major brand equipment utilizing off-shore 3rd party manufacturers.<\/p>\n<p>Please compare the certification labels on your own race shoes and suits against the photographs below.<\/p>\n<p>Take note in the difference in fonts on the shoe labels, and that there\u00a0is an incorrect word on one of the shoe labels.<\/p>\n<p>In addition to the difference in the quality of embroidery on the suit patches, the reverse side of the counterfeit suit patches has a felt covering that is not present on the genuine patches.<\/p>\n<p>There are also label security measures which are not visible in a photograph, which SFI uses to identify genuine versus fake labels.<\/p>\n<p>Please contact the SFI Foundation (<a href=\"&#109;a&#x69;l&#x74;o&#x3a;s&#x66;i&#x40;s&#x66;&#105;&#x66;&#111;&#x75;&#110;&#x64;&#97;&#x74;&#105;&#x6f;&#110;&#x2e;&#99;o&#x6d;\">&#x73;&#102;i&#x40;&#x73;&#102;i&#x66;&#x6f;&#117;n&#x64;&#97;t&#x69;&#x6f;&#110;&#46;&#x63;&#x6f;&#109;<\/a>) if you suspect fraud or counterfeit items.<\/p>\n<p>Download a PDF version of this notice here: <a href=\"http:\/\/sfifoundation.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/SFINotice11-10-16.pdf\">SFINotice11-10-16<\/a>. This blog post can also be shared to your social media pages via the below share buttons.<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft size-large wp-i